Cookie helper:
```ts
const COOKIE_NAME = 'sk_session';
const COOKIE_OPTS = `HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax; Path=/; Max-Age=${60 * 60 * 24 * 30}${
  process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production' ? '; Secure' : ''
}`;

function setCookie(res: NextResponse, token: string) {
  res.headers.set('Set-Cookie', `${COOKIE_NAME}=${token}; ${COOKIE_OPTS}`);
}
function clearCookie(res: NextResponse) {
  res.headers.set('Set-Cookie', `${COOKIE_NAME}=; HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax; Path=/; Max-Age=0`);
}
```

The handler reads the existing `sk_session` cookie and passes it as
`Authorization: Bearer <value>` to NestJS for authenticated proxied calls (logout, me).

The handler returns the full NestJS response body to the browser (including `token` for
in-memory seeding), plus the `Set-Cookie` header. Login's `requiresTwoFactor: true`
branch gets no cookie set (no session exists yet).

